<h1>Trauma</h1>
<p>Traumatic events can have immediate, unexpected, and long-lasting effects on a person. Cook Counseling Center recognizes this and has created the following documents for the university community about dealing with trauma. If you would like to speak to a counselor about any issue that you are currently dealing with, contact us.</p>
<ul>
	<li><a href="https://www.ucc.vt.edu/content/dam/ucc_vt_edu/assets/docs/dealing_with_aftermath_tragedy_in_classroom.pdf" target="_blank">Dealing with the Aftermath of Tragedy in the Classroom (PDF | 25KB)</a></li>
	<li><a href="https://www.ucc.vt.edu/content/dam/ucc_vt_edu/assets/docs/suggestions_for_faculty_staff_when_dealing_with_tragedy.pdf" target="_blank">Suggestions for Faculty and Staff When Dealing with a Tragedy (PDF | 13KB)</a></li>
	<li><a href="https://ucc.vt.edu/about/appointments/faculty_information.html" target="_blank">Faculty and Staff Information on Identifying and Referring a Distressed Student</a></li>
</ul>
